_:N41df9c889c554109bbcdbf18c7d40c38 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Independent Water Commission was established in October 2024 to deliver recommendations to government on reforms to the water sector.</p>\n\n<p>It is chaired by Former Deputy Governor of the Bank of England, Sir Jon Cunliffe.</p>\n\n<p>The Commission is focused on ensuring there is a sufficiently robust and stable regulatory framework to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>attract the investment needed for the future</li>\n  <li>speed up infrastructure delivery</li>\n  <li>restore confidence in the sector</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>As set out in the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/independent-commission-on-the-water-sector-regulatory-system-terms-of-reference\">Terms of Reference</a>, the Commission is operating independently of the UK and Welsh Ministers.</p>\n\n<p>The Chair and advisory group are supported by a Defra Secretariat.</p>\n</div>" .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/independent-water-commission> <http://schema.org/name> "Independent Water Commission" .
